---
description: Repository structure, modules, and how pieces fit together
---

# Monorepo layout

- app/
  - Nuxt 4 application (frontend + server API)
  - Prisma schema and migrations
  - Server clients (Prisma/Redis/NATS/Postmark/OpenAI), services, queues, cron
  - Tests: unit/integration (Vitest) and E2E (Playwright)
- microservice/
  - Lightweight Nitro/H3 server used for maintenance and encryption key rotation workflows
  - Its own Prisma schema subset and field-encryption migrators
- scripts/
  - Local automation, DB restore helpers, key rotation, coverage helpers
- .deploy/
  - Kubernetes templates for app/microservice and staging key-rotation cronjob + RBAC
- .github/
  - Actions to build/push Docker images to GCR and deploy to GKE (PR → staging, main → production)

# Application (app/) structure

Frontend (Nuxt 4)
- pages/ — route views (e.g., account registers, reoccurrences, goals, admin)
- components/ — UI components and modals
- stores/ — Pinia stores (authStore, listStore)
- composables/ — reusable client/server composables (API fetchers, filters, workflow/snapshot modes)
- assets/ — CSS (Tailwind)
- plugins/ — initialization hooks (api client, disable lastpass, store init, snapshot menu)
- layouts/, app.vue — Nuxt shell

Server (Nitro/H3 inside app/)
- server/api/ — API handlers; filename suffix encodes method (.get.ts, .post.ts, .patch.ts, .delete.ts)
- server/lib/ — helpers for auth, sessions, pagination, error handling, rate limiting, logging, Plaid helpers, etc.
- server/middleware/ — auth gate and http middlewares
- server/clients/ — prismaClient, redisClient, queuesClient, postmarkClient, openaiClient, natsClient
- server/services/ — domain services:
  - forecast/* — ForecastEngine orchestration + services (DataLoader, AccountRegister, Reoccurrence, RegisterEntry, LoanCalculator, Transfer, DateTime/ModernCache) and tests
  - PlaidSyncService, PlaidTransactionEnrichmentService, PlaidSyncNotificationService
  - TransactionMatchingService, NotificationCenterService
  - reconciliationService, reports/CategoryReportService, billCenterService, budgetCloneService, accountInvite/member services, etc.
  - crypto: AlchemyService, AssetValueEstimateService
- server/queues/ — BullMQ queues (backup, plaidSync, recalculate)
- server/cron/ — scheduled jobs (plaid daily/hourly, balance sync hourly, backup daily, bill reminders hourly, recalculate hourly, crypto balance hourly)
- server/routes/ — custom route shims (health, _nuxt assets, sitemap)
- server/env.ts, envSchema.ts — configuration loader and Zod validation

Data layer
- prisma/schema.prisma — full domain schema (MySQL provider; Decimal types for amounts)
- prisma/migrations/* — generated SQL migrations (large, incremental domain evolution)
- prisma/reencrypt/* — generated migrators for prisma-field-encryption
- prisma/prismaClient.ts — app-level Prisma init and extension
- prisma/seed.ts — seed logic (accounts, intervals, categories, etc.)

Testing
- server/api/__tests__ — broad test suites for endpoints
- server/services/**/__tests__ — service-level tests (forecast engine, matching, etc.)
- lib/__tests__ and schema/__tests__ — utility and schema tests
- pages/__tests__/ — simple route tests
- tests/e2e/** — Playwright UI specs (public + authed), plus screenshots

# Microservice (microservice/)

Purpose
- Operational support. Evidenced uses include DB field-encryption key rotation (K8S CronJob "runner-keyrotate" image) and a simple /migrate endpoint.

Structure
- server.ts and server/logger.ts — Nitro/H3 server bootstrap
- routes/migrate.get.ts, migrate.post.ts, test.get.ts — minimal endpoints
- prisma/schema.prisma — subset schema aligned to app for the relevant encrypted models and intervals/types
- prisma/reencrypt/ — generated migrators for prisma-field-encryption
- clients/ — prismaClient, redisClient; lib/bull.ts helpers

# How it fits together

- UI → app/server/api → domain services → Prisma (MySQL) and Redis
- Background jobs (queues/*) and cron (cron/*) handle syncs (Plaid, crypto), cache rebuilds, backups, bill reminders
- Forecast engine composes services to compute register balances/entries over time using in-memory caches and typed time helpers
- Field-level encryption keeps sensitive data protected; generated re-encryptors are used for rotation and post-restore workflows
- Microservice can be driven by a CronJob to rotate DB encryption keys and trigger app-side migration flows
- CI builds two images (app and microservice), pushes to GCR, and GKE deploys them with configs from .deploy templates; readiness/liveness gates are provided via /health/ready and /health/live
